The paper deals with the semantics of strategic games and their representation using coalgebras. This makes it likely to belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of coalgebras to represent complex social systems of cognitive agents, which suggests that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) categories. The paper also deals with game theory, which makes it likely to belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of verification and logical tools of software engineering, which suggests that it could also belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DS) category.
